gov.usgs.anss.aftac

Class AftacHoldingsServer

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • gov.usgs.anss.aftac.AftacHoldingsServer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class AftacHoldingsServer
extends java.lang.Thread
    This server returns holdings reported in Aftac format. Normally it runs on port 29050. The command syntax is : *
    
 Option :
  -h host   Override host from MySQLServer property to be host
 -p port     Override port from 29050

  Command line input format:
     -s stationRegExp The station regular express in NSCL order
     -b begindate Can be all, for yyyy,ddd-hh:mm:ss or yyyy/mm/dd-hh:mm:ss
     -e enddate Same form as begindate
     -d duration nnnnn[dD] assumed seconds unless "d" is present
